    <h1>Professions</h1>
    <p>Professions are meant to collect and produce and they help you on your journey. With these you can make armor, weapons and other stuff. 
        You can have two (2) professions on you at the same time. You can also unlearn them if you think you no longer need them.

    </p>

    <h2>Gathering:</h2>
    <p>With gathering professions you can gather ores, herbs or fish. These can be used with production professions or you can sell these items.</p>
    <h3>Mining</h3>
    <p>Mine ore veins for different kind of minerals which can be used in either Jewelcraft or Blacksmithing.</p> 
    <h3>Fishing</h3>
    <p>Fish your food from lakes and sell them or cook them for later use.</p>
    <h3>Herbalist</h3>
    <p>
       Collect different kinds of herbs and make them into powerful potions which help you in your battles to come.
    </p>
    <h2>Production:</h2>
    <p>
        With production professions you can make yourself armor, weapons and much more! These items can be either used yourself or sold.
    </p>
    <h3>Runescripter</h3>
    <p>
        As a Runescripter you can make śpellbooks, teleport tabelts and also enchantments.
    </p>
    <h3>Tailor</h3>
    <p>
        As a Tailor you can make cloth armors for Acolyte and Ritualist related classes.
    </p>
    <h3>Blacksmith</h3>
    <p>
        As a Blacksmith you can make heavy armor for Fighter related classes.
    </p>
    <h3>Jewelcraft</h3>
    <p>
        As a Jewelcraft you can make amulets and rings which gives you boosts for attributes or skills.
    </p>
    <h3>Chef</h3>
    <p>
        As a chef you can cook food which heal you and give you stat bonuses.
    </p>
    <h3>Woodcraft</h3>
    <p>
        Woodcraft is something special. You can also get your wood with this. So it's both gathering and production profession. But it also requires both. 
        So you can only have it and not the other profession with it.

    </p>
